--- [RESPONSE] (9.2s) ---
### File Structure
```
CarRental/
│
├── app.py
├── templates/
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── vehicle_search.html
│   ├── vehicle_details.html
│   ├── booking.html
│   ├── insurance.html
│   ├── rental_history.html
│   ├── reservations.html
│   ├── special_requests.html
│   └── locations.html
│
├── static/
│   ├── css/
│   │   └── styles.css
│   ├── js/
│   │   └── scripts.js
│   └── images/
│       └── (vehicle images, icons, etc.)
│
└── data/
    ├── vehicles.txt
    ├── customers.txt
    ├── locations.txt
    ├── rentals.txt
    ├── insurance.txt
    └── reservations.txt
```

### File Descriptions
- **app.py**  
  The main backend Python application file. It handles all routing, business logic, data reading/writing from/to the local text files in the `data/` directory, and serves the HTML templates. Since the application is not very complex, all backend logic (including vehicle search, booking, insurance selection, reservation management, rental history, special requests, and locations handling) will be implemented here.

- **templates/**  
  Directory containing all HTML template files for the web application pages, each corresponding to one of the nine pages specified in the requirements:
  - `dashboard.html`: Dashboard page with featured vehicles, promotions, and navigation buttons.
  - `vehicle_search.html`: Vehicle search page with filters and vehicle listings.
  - `vehicle_details.html`: Detailed vehicle information page.
  - `booking.html`: Booking page for rental details input.
  - `insurance.html`: Insurance options selection page.
  - `rental_history.html`: Rental history display page.
  - `reservations.html`: Reservation management page.
  - `special_requests.html`: Special requests input page.
  - `locations.html`: Pickup and dropoff locations page.

- **static/**  
  Contains static assets used by the web pages:
  - `css/styles.css`: Stylesheet for consistent styling across pages.
  - `js/scripts.js`: JavaScript for client-side interactivity (e.g., date pickers, dynamic filtering).
  - `images/`: Folder for vehicle images, icons, and other graphical assets.

- **data/**  
  Stores all application data in text files as specified:
  - `vehicles.txt`: Vehicle data.
  - `customers.txt`: Customer data.
  - `locations.txt`: Rental locations data.
  - `rentals.txt`: Rental transactions data.
  - `insurance.txt`: Insurance plans data.
  - `reservations.txt`: Reservation data.

This structure cleanly separates backend logic, frontend templates, static resources, and data storage, facilitating maintainability and scalability while meeting the project requirements.
